<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1440,1499,1920]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1859,1884]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Distribution.</emphasis>
Although currently known only from the above localities in shelf depths (
<quantity box="[1235,1371,1859,1884]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.55" metricValueMax="2.6" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" unit="m" value="255.0" valueMax="260.0" valueMin="250.0">250–260 m</quantity>
), this species may be more widespread in Japanese waters, where it might have been confused with 
<emphasis box="[1204,1334,1895,1920]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Muller" baseAuthorityYear="1776" box="[1204,1329,1895,1920]" class="Polychaeta" family="Flabelligeridae" genus="Pherusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="plumosa">P. plumosa</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
